{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "1 are specially finetuned on target datasets to achieve VideoQA.",
    "Models in the 2nd block are general-purpose Video-LLMs and most of they do a zero-shot evaluation on VideoQA.",
    "As exception, VideoChat2 (Li et al., 2023b) includes the training data of NExT-QA (Xiao et al., 2021) (one of our major testbed) for instruction tuning, and thus should be considered a normal evaluation versus zero-shot.",
    "Also, for Video-LLaMA, we adopt the implementation in (Xiao et al., 2024), which is finetuned on NExT-QA by adding adpation parameters as in LLaMA-Adapter (Zhang et al., 2023c).",
    "Additionally, we include the recent GPT-4o (OpenAI, 2023) as a representative of commercial models for off-theshelf use."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As exception, VideoChat2 (Li et al., 2023b) includes the training data of NExT-QA (Xiao et al., 2021) (one of our major testbed) for instruction tuning, and thus should be considered a normal evaluation versus zero-shot.",
    "Also, for Video-LLaMA, we adopt the implementation in (Xiao et al., 2024), which is finetuned on NExT-QA by adding adpation parameters as in LLaMA-Adapter (Zhang et al., 2023c).",
    "Additionally, we include the recent GPT-4o (OpenAI, 2023) as a representative of commercial models for off-theshelf use."
